reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good. Durable. Screws into outlet. A nice feature.
reviews.reviewText: I like that it screws into the outlet so that you do not have it pulling out when you try to unplug something. Has USB and USB C. It is very sturdy and looks good. The only thing I don't like is that this is using only one plug on the wall outlet to run all of this. I guess it doesn't matter for most things that you plug in but I would be careful what you plug into it. It is possible to overload it. But for low voltage devices it shouldn't be a problem. It has a green indicator light that lets you know it is working. Great for plugging in multiple things into a single outlet. It does have a surge protector. So far have not tripped it. A good deal. Better than expected.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Works well, looks nice, extremely useful, and affordable. What's not to like??
reviews.reviewText: I've bought a number of outlet expanders over the years and the early ones were terrible. Big, bulky, ugly and only added an extra outlet spot or 2.The QINLIANF 5 Outlet Extender is much more advanced, attractive and powerful than any other I have tried. It adds 3 additional full outlets to any plug, as well as 3 USB outlets and one USB-C outlet. Admittedly, I have not used the USB-C outlet yet, but I have chargers and cords plugged into pretty much all of the other outlets including an Amazon Echo, chargers for a tablet, iPad, cell phone and portable speaker.It can be installed permanently by using the middle screw to anchor it to the outlet (once the faceplate has been removed, an extremely easy DIY project) or simply plugged in like any other device and then removed and moved around if needed.Honestly, when I bought it, I didn't realize that is also has a built in surge protector. I haven't had use for it yet, thankfullly, but it's nice to know it's there standing guard for me. There is a green light in the middle, although I don't know what its function is. Perhaps something to do with the surge protector.Overall, it is a great outlet extender and I will be buying several more for around the house, since, with a family of 5, there are endless devices and chargers that need plugging in.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quick Fix for Cord Clutter
reviews.reviewText: Tired of having my cords all over the floor this surge protector was a great buy! This surge protector not only provides multiple outlets but also offers robust surge protection, ensuring your devices are shielded from power fluctuations. With features like USB ports for convenient charging and a sleek design, it not only protects but also enhances your setup. Don't compromise on the safety of your electronics; this surge protector is a reliable and essential investment for anyone looking to secure their devices and maintain peace of mind.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Odd stud, but it's still a great unit!
reviews.reviewText: The reason why that I say it is "odd" is because it won't just plug into your outlet - there is some kind of plastic stud (?) that sticks up and must be broken off before it'll plug in; it broke off with a little bit of effort but not so much that I would consider it hard to remove. And once you get it plugged in and lock it down (with the long screw that comes in the box) that's in the middle it's tight to the wall, secure and it works great. We all love it!And it's really awesome that you have multiple USB ports on it so that you can charge your phones or whatever else or just plug in your phone or whatever to play sooner music while you're doing dishes or cleaning and then you don't have to worry about the batteries draining down (and it will obviously charge your phone or whatever while you have it plugged in playing the music). The plug outlets are arranged in a great pattern too, easy to use formatting.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This covers all the chargeable units in our home. Many option ports available and not too bulky or gaudy looking installed on kitchen counter top (prime area for us). So far no problems and functions as described in every way.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024

This has much more room, the USB ports work nicely, and looks way better than a huge rectangle laying in the floor. Great product, especially on sale. The screw to hold it in place for duplex outlets was a nice touch.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars GREAT Surge Protection, USB ports, outlet spacing and price! Standard (not fast speed) USB C charge
reviews.reviewText: So, this surge protector and power strip has a lot of protection when it comes to surge protection! At the top end of what you will find for general electronics, this one has 1680 joules of protection before it gets fried to save everything thats plugged into it. If you have any high end gaming computers, REALLY expensive electronics, you would purchase an expensive/entire next level surge protector having over 2000 (2K) joules of protection. So this surge protector packs a punch for all regular electronics, regular computer equipment.The lit up center green button shows that the surge protection is still working and has not been fried by a lightening hit or something. If it does one day get fried, this whole unit will still work as a power strip but would no longer provide the surge protection for the devices plugged into it.I mounted this charger and plugged in some "hard to plug in" electrical cords and this thing held sturdy! I was impressed at how sturdy it was when I had to really give an extra push or pull to some of my plugs going into or pulling out of it.Each of the three USB A (same as saying USB) port is 12 Watts. This matches the highest capacity of most USB A cords, so this is good. It also is great that EACH USB A port has this capacity, so plugging in multiple devices into these ports will not create a slow down on the others, which is great!The one USB C port is 15 Watts but not a fast charging port. So it may take 56 minutes to charge the same as what a fast charger would take 34 minutes, as an accurate example. I am fine with that.. But good to be aware that this will not charge as fast as a "fast charger" if you have one of those elsewhere in the house. And if you do, you could always plug that fast charger into one of the traditional outlets on this power strip and achieve your fast charging effect that way!The traditional electrical ports are well spaced and VERY handy.The price is GREAT! A GREAT bargain!This purchase is an excellent one!

reviews.reviewTitle: Excellent product I love it. Can be fixed into the outlet with screw.
reviews.reviewText: Best feature on this multiplug is that it can be mounted into the wall plate of the wall outlet. Which means it fixes securely and doesn’t move when you are plugging and unplugging devices. I love that feature. Also has surge protection which is great. The quality is good and having usb-A and usb-c outlets is very handy and they seem to be efficient at charging devices quicker. All in all, I love this product and highly recommend it.

This outlet/charger is well designed, well made and very useful. It stays very secure when plugged over a wall plate that is attached with two screws or the ones that have a screw in the middle. The outlets in an angle is a great idea as it saves space and protect the plugs attached to it. Having the USB c included is great. I am happy with it and highly recommend.

reviews.reviewTitle: Works great no more power bar on the floor
reviews.reviewText: The only down side is that we have wall plugs that do not have a screw in the middle so we can't secure it but it does stay in anyway. Never look for a usb charger anymore, it always there
Great value for the money, great item, very useful.

exactly what I wanted. USB ports are handy, but feels a bit slow when charging devices compared to using manufacturers charger. I used the long screw to secure it to the wall plug and it holds very well.Too bulky to put behind furniture.
